text: Calangianus (Caragnàni, Calanzànos) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sassari in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 4,121 people lived there. Its area is 126.35 km². It is 518 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of Sassari
